{
  "stem": "13096.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Each one, you know, they prepared their own meal, but we came to a house where there was room for everybody, and we were just having the meals together.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everybody on Rhodes Island was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, they were very religious.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We used to go-- you know, in Rhodes Island, there used to be two major synagogue.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One, it was called the Kahale Shalom, and the other one was called the Kahal Grande, which, it means in English, the [INAUDIBLE] Shul, the [INAUDIBLE] Shul.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And all of the Jewish people lived on Rhodes Island belonged to one or the other one.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we belonged to Shalom, Kahal Shalom.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The rabbi at the time when I-- when I was, it was Mr.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Vital ?] that he later immigrate to Israel and later-- and later on in life it was a rabbi called Albagli, A-L-B-A-G-L-I.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we used to have all day Jewish ritual.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First of all, we used to put, you know, the meat and all this, in, you know, in salt and all this like [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then every Friday night, we used to have, you know, the nice meal.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And nobody was allowed to touch electricity or to open a-- you know, a stove or whatever.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the-- the festival, let's just say, everybody, you know, was not working on Saturday, on Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "All day, Jewish-- the Jewish shops were closed on Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And you can see it was like a day of-- of Sabbath because the whole commerce in Rhodes Island was done by the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then, when they closed on Saturday, it was dead.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Nobody was in the-- in the shops because nobody went to shop any more because it was not worth it.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
